ariably got lost, the necks would dry up, and when he pressed too hard the tube would burst at the bottom and thence would come crawling and writhing a fat worm of goo. His daubings were fruitless and even the simplest things — a vase with flowers or a sunset copied from a travel folder of the Riviera — came out spotty, sickly, horrible.

